One more interesting outcome of our work is the possible implementation of an artificial magnetic field acting on photons35. Indeed, the effect of the OA in the Hamiltonian (4) with zero β0 can be represented as an action of a vector potential, opposite for the two spin components (±)7Ĥ±=12mp̂−eA±2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
